rules for test class naming. The existing file name is `RequestSpecificationImplInner_applyRestAssuredConfig_closure20Test.java`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class name and method issues**\\n\\nI'm considering if adding an underscore after \\\"Inner\\\" in the class name is acceptable. Maybe the methods didn't execute because one test failed early on? If compilerGeneratedClassResolver doesn't support a catch, it might not cover properly. I'm curious about why it's unsupported in the JVM. Perhaps `privateLookupIn(closureClass, lookup)` is failing due to the module/package situation, but since the class is package-private, I wonder if the classloader should still work.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing Java Reflection and Instrumentation**\\n\\nI'm looking into a situation where `javap` indicates that a method is package-private. I'm using `findStatic` with a specific method type, but I wonder if it throws a `NoSuchMethodException` in a native context. It seems that dynamic access coverage may only track calls made through dynamically instrumented classes, not direct calls to hidden methods from an uninstrumented JAR. The tests might be running against Maven dependencies instead of the instrumented version. It's puzzling that existing tests invoke this method but still report false. It might be due to private static methods not being covered properly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Test Refinement Mechanisms**\\n\\nI'm focused on an active task that involves adding or refining tests. I need to find a way to trigger `class$` through Groovy’s call site creation, possibly by using older bytecode class literals. I'm wondering why `javap` shows `ldc` instead of `class$`, possibly due to a Java 8 target. It's curious that `class$` is generated but remains unused. Maybe it could be linked to a custom `MetaClass` when calling `$getStaticMetaClass` with a different subclass. I’ll inspect `javap` with verbose options for references to `class$`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_QvtxLmyl24gIWUJ1Q5JSG2dO|fc_08185052b1b9d476016a00c536da1481979b0e9975e12b6337", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap -classpath tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/build/jacoco/effective/rest_assured_5_5_0_jar -c -p -verbose 'io.restassured.internal.RequestSpecificationImpl$_applyRestAssuredConfig_closure20' | rg -n \"class\\$|#122|forName|invokestatic\" -C 2"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 872, "output": 1448, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30992, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778435356278, "responseId": "resp_08185052b1b9d476016a00c51cd2cc8197b379e6ebba439b97"}}
